=head1 Gnome::Gtk4::FontChooserWidget

![](images/fontchooserwidget.png)

=head1 Description

The B<Gnome::Gtk4::FontChooserWidget> widget lets the user select a font.

It is used in the B<Gnome::Gtk4::FontChooserDialog> widget to provide a
dialog for selecting fonts.

To set the font which is initially selected, use
C<.set-font() in class Gnome::Gtk4::R-FontChooser> or C<.set-font-desc() in class Gnome::Gtk4::R-FontChooser>.

To get the selected font use C<.get-font() in class Gnome::Gtk4::R-FontChooser> or
C<.get-font-desc() in class Gnome::Gtk4::R-FontChooser>.

To change the text which is shown in the preview area, use
C<.set-preview-text() in class Gnome::Gtk4::R-FontChooser>.

=head2 CSS nodes

B<Gnome::Gtk4::FontChooserWidget> has a single CSS node with name fontchooser.

